## ğŸŒ¤ï¸ Variable: `LIGHT_CONDITION` â€” Lighting Condition

### ğŸ“˜ Definition  
This variable describes the lighting environment at the time of the crash or near-miss event. Lighting condition can significantly influence the perception capability of both human drivers and autonomous vehicles, especially in edge-case scenarios.

---

### ğŸ§© Label Options

| Value                | Description                                             |
|----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| `daylight`           | Daytime with natural sunlight; scene is clearly visible |
| `dark with light`    | Nighttime with sufficient artificial illumination (e.g., street lights, vehicle headlights) |
| `dark without light` | Nighttime without visible illumination; environment appears dark with limited visibility |

